docs.abstract: Are you an online star with more than 500,000 followers? Jeffrey Katzenberg may want to have a word with you.
docs.snippet: Are you an online star with more than 500,000 followers? Jeffrey Katzenberg may want to have a word with you.
docs.lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — Jeffrey Katzenberg and Meg Whitman, the founders of Quibi, a short-form video app scheduled for an April 6 debut, are trying to create a platform for the smartphone age. To entice subscribers, they have ordered big-budget shows from known quantities like Kevin Hart and Steven Spielberg — but they have turned to social media stars for the kind of casual, low-commitment programming that could make Quibi a daily habit.

headline.main: Release the Influencers! Quibi’s Plan for Streaming Success
headline.print_headline: Streaming Platform Quibi Is Banking on Influencers

docs.abstract: The morning co-anchor, a Fox News veteran, will host a daily newscast at 3 p.m. But don’t expect Smith-style fireworks.
docs.snippet: The morning co-anchor, a Fox News veteran, will host a daily newscast at 3 p.m. But don’t expect Smith-style fireworks.
docs.lead_paragraph: Fox News on Monday named Bill Hemmer, one of the network’s longest-serving news anchors, to replace Shepard Smith as host of the channel’s 3 p.m. weekday newscast.

headline.main: Fox News Picks Bill Hemmer to Take Shepard Smith’s Old Slot
headline.print_headline: Hemmer Gets  The Time Slot Held by Smith At Fox News

docs.abstract: In a legal complaint, Amazon said the president had attacked it behind the scenes to harm its C.E.O., Jeff Bezos, “his perceived political enemy.”
docs.snippet: In a legal complaint, Amazon said the president had attacked it behind the scenes to harm its C.E.O., Jeff Bezos, “his perceived political enemy.”
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Amazon said in a legal complaint unsealed on Monday that it had lost a $10 billion cloud computing contract with the Pentagon because President Trump used “improper pressure” to divert the contract from the company to harm its chief executive, Jeff Bezos.

headline.main: Amazon Accuses Trump of ‘Improper Pressure’ on JEDI Contract

docs.abstract: The latest effort to rework a program for borrowers whose schools broke the law drew an immediate promise of a court challenge.
docs.snippet: The latest effort to rework a program for borrowers whose schools broke the law drew an immediate promise of a court challenge.
docs.lead_paragraph: Thousands of students who took out federal loans to attend schools that lured them with fraudulent claims will still have to repay a portion of their debts, the Education Department said Tuesday — a new attempt to water down a loan-forgiveness program that the department’s leader has long deplored.

headline.main: DeVos Tries Again to Cut Debt Relief for Students Who Were Misled
headline.print_headline: DeVos Again Tries to Limit Loan Relief

docs.abstract: The central bank is expected to keep rates steady at its final meeting of 2019. Investors want to know how long the pause will last.
docs.snippet: The central bank is expected to keep rates steady at its final meeting of 2019. Investors want to know how long the pause will last.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Federal Reserve is expected to leave interest rates unchanged at its final meeting of the year on Wednesday as officials wait to see how the economy fares after they cut rate three times in 2019.

headline.main: A Preview of the December Fed Meeting

docs.abstract: The technology investment powerhouse sold its shares as its pushes the companies it bets on to seek profits and long-term stability.
docs.snippet: The technology investment powerhouse sold its shares as its pushes the companies it bets on to seek profits and long-term stability.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — The SoftBank Vision Fund has sold its stake in Wag, the troubled dog-walking start-up, back to the company at a loss, according to two people briefed on the deal, in a further sign of turmoil for the Japanese investment powerhouse that has bet big and lost big on the technologies of the future.

headline.main: SoftBank Takes Loss in Sale of Wag, Dog-Walking Start-Up
headline.print_headline: SoftBank Absorbs Loss And Sells Back Its Stake In Dog-Walking Start-Up

docs.abstract: With 1.5 billion users, Facebook’s WhatsApp is perhaps the world’s most commonly used encrypted communications platform.
docs.snippet: With 1.5 billion users, Facebook’s WhatsApp is perhaps the world’s most commonly used encrypted communications platform.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Facebook executives and Attorney General William P. Barr sparred on Monday over whether encrypted messaging products should be open to law enforcement, escalating a standoff over privacy and policing.

headline.main: Facebook and Barr Escalate Standoff Over Encrypted Messages
headline.print_headline: Facebook and Barr Joust  Over Encryption Products

docs.abstract: Aramco, the world’s largest oil company, set a price for its shares that marks the company’s value at $1.7 trillion.
docs.snippet: Aramco, the world’s largest oil company, set a price for its shares that marks the company’s value at $1.7 trillion.
docs.lead_paragraph: Saudi Arabia’s giant state-owned oil company, Saudi Aramco, on Thursday set the price of its initial public offering at a level that would raise $25.6 billion, a sum that is expected to make it the world’s biggest I.P.O.

headline.main: Saudi Aramco to Raise $25.6 Billion in Biggest I.P.O. Ever

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The head of the Federal Aviation Administration said on Wednesday that his agency had made mistakes in its handling of the crashes of two Boeing 737 Max jets and that the planes, which remain grounded, would not fly again this year.

docs.abstract: The indie distributor Neon has Oscar contenders with Bong Joon Ho’s latest and the documentary “Apollo 11.”
docs.snippet: The indie distributor Neon has Oscar contenders with Bong Joon Ho’s latest and the documentary “Apollo 11.”
docs.lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — It was not a surprise that critics would love “Parasite,” the latest film from the acclaimed director Bong Joon Ho. But box-office success for this sometimes funny, sometimes horrifying Korean-language tale of economic inequality was no sure thing. Enter Tom Quinn, the head of Neon, a rising independent film distributor and production company.

headline.main: ‘Parasite’ Has Shocked the Box Office, Helped by an Upstart Studio
headline.print_headline: The Upstart Indie Studio With an Eye for Success
